==Ingredient== * 1 1/2 cup all-purpose flour * 1/2 tsp salt * 1/2 tsp baking soda * 1/2 cup butter * 1/4 cup brown sugar * 1/2 granulated sugar * 1 egg * 1 tsp vanilla essence * 1 pack or 6 ounce of semi-sweet chocolate chip
==Procedure== # Combine the flour, salt, & baking powder. Preheat the oven until it reaches 375 degrees. # In another bowl, cream the butter & the sugars until it looks light & fluffy. # Beat in the flour mixture until it's well-blended. # Add the chocolate chips & stir with a wooden spoon. # Drop the cookies in a lightly greased cookie sheet or lined with parchment paper by teaspoonfuls in 2-inch ball shapes. # Bake for 15 minutes or until the edge's are light brown. # Take the cookies from the cookie sheet with a metal spatula, then let them cool in wire rack.

